{"cursor":"6650","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n clapperboard in use]]\n\n\nA 'clapperboard' is a device used in filmmaking and video production to assist\nin the synchronizing of picture and sound, and to designate and mark particular\nscenes and takes recorded during a production. The sharp \"clap\" noise that the\nclapperboard makes can be identified easily on the audio track, and the shutting\nof the clapstick can be identified easily on the separate visual track. The two\ntracks can then be precisely synchronised by matching the sound and movement.\nOther names for the clapperboard include 'clapper', 'clapboard', 'slate', 'slate\nboard', 'sync slate', 'time slate', 'sticks', 'board', and 'marker'.\n\nWhen a movie's sound and picture are out of synchronization, this is known\nas lip flap.\n","linknr":162,"url":"Clapperboard","recorded":1362671383,"links":37,"instances":["fiction","writing","film"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Film and video technology"],"headings":["Overview","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Clapperboardinuse.jpg/220px-Clapperboardinuse.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/2009-06-23-flemming-by-RalfR-20.jpg/220px-2009-06-23-flemming-by-RalfR-20.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/33/Clapperboard%2C_O2_film%2C_September_2008.jpg/200px-Clapperboard%2C_O2_film%2C_September_2008.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/A_Traditional_Wooden_Slate_Clapperboard.jpg/200px-A_Traditional_Wooden_Slate_Clapperboard.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Clapperboard.jpg/200px-Clapperboard.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/37px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["scene","fiction"],["scene","fiction"],["mos","film"],["slate","writing"]],"members":["scene","slate","mos"],"related":["Filmmaking","Video_production","Scene_(fiction)","Take","Lip_flap","Whiteboard","Acrylic_glass","SMPTE_time_code","Light-emitting_diode","Digital","Take","Film_director","Director_of_photography","Scene_(fiction)","Camera_angle","Take","Take","Multiple-camera_setup","Clapper_loader","Script_supervisor","Clapper_loader","MOS_(film)","Frank_Thring","Efftee_Studios","Melbourne","Australia","Digital","Google_Patents","LED","Slate_(writing)"]}